This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with collaborative filtering algorithms used in recommendation systems. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it examines the distribution of gender in user rating profiles and recommendation lists. Additionally, it could be classified under Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it discusses ethical concerns related to discrimination. The paper also touches upon issues related to social justice, which could place it under the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category. Finally, it may be classified under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with natural language processing in the context of book ratings.
